","affiliations":[],"outcome_text":"00:48:45","overall_rank":9,"result_notes":"Source note: 6 correct.","category_name":"Bike","category_rank":null,"individual_id":"019b7b5f-d72e-71e1-9b77-0b5a3942e771","metric_summary":null,"competitor_name":"Terry Farrah","competitor_type":"individual","additional_course":false,"affiliation_labels":[]}],"course_id":"019d3384-2fa8-76a7-98d4-80e0906105ae","course_name":"Wheel of Fortune","distance_km":null,"result_count":10,"control_count":null,"course_climb_m":null}],"event_id":"019b81b3-75e2-7d3b-ace1-487507018162","venue_id":"019b80fa-1f49-7aac-af1e-a26a076d1964","event_date":"2005-08-19","event_kind":"race","event_name":"Ballard Bike-O","venue_name":"Ballard","event_notes":null,"course_count":4,"event_status":null,"result_count":24,"citation_count":1,"event_comments":"Much thanks to Ben Hall, Terry Farrah, and Eric Bone for helping run the meet, and to Don Atkinson for bringing the supplies.\nWe had 25 groups for a total of about 50 participants. It was good to see many newcomers.\nThe towns were: Manitowoc WI, Tucumcari NM, Bogalusa LA, Winnemucca NV, Pocatello ID, Kokomo IN, Punxsutawney PA, and Schenectady NY\nDick & Kim (no results)\nEric was awarded 3 minutes for discovering and re-hanging a misplaced control.\nBen visited all of the points, but switched the boxes for I and H. He claims that he was going so fast around the corners that he was tilted horizontal to the ground. Thus the I looked like an H and vice versa. I'm sure he and Alex will have many joyful discussions about who really won.","external_links":[],"volunteer_roles":[{"role_name":"Course Setter","individual_id":"019b811c-3e18-7e4f-84b5-4159730958fb","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Pat Kelly","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null},{"role_name":"Meet Director","individual_id":"019b811c-3e18-7e4f-84b5-4159730958fb","citation_count":1,"individual_name":"Pat Kelly","volunteer_hours":null,"volunteer_points":null}],"organizing_club_id":"01912f3e-e3e1-7e8e-b3c6-32387a8b4990","result_source_brief":"Older COC Results Website: http://www.old.cascadeoc.org/Results2005/20050710.html","organizing_club_name":"Cascade Orienteering Club","cumulative_event_comments":"Much thanks to Ben Hall, Terry Farrah, and Eric Bone for helping run the meet, and to Don Atkinson for bringing the supplies.\nWe had 25 groups for a total of about 50 participants. It was good to see many newcomers.\nThe towns were: Manitowoc WI, Tucumcari NM, Bogalusa LA, Winnemucca NV, Pocatello ID, Kokomo IN, Punxsutawney PA, and Schenectady NY\nDick & Kim (no results)\nEric was awarded 3 minutes for discovering and re-hanging a misplaced control.\nBen visited all of the points, but switched the boxes for I and H. He claims that he was going so fast around the corners that he was tilted horizontal to the ground. Thus the I looked like an H and vice versa. I'm sure he and Alex will have many joyful discussions about who really won."}
